==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Holt
<hw>Holt</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>holt</ets>; akin to LG.
<ets>holt</ets>, D. <ets>hout</ets>, G. <ets>holz</ets>. Icel.
<ets>holt</ets>; cf Gael. & Ir. <ets>coill</ets> wood, Gr. <?/ branch,
shoot.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A piece of woodland; especially, a woody
hill.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Every <xex>holt</xex> and heath.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She sent her voice though all the holt⟦br⟧
Before her, and the park.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A deep hole in a river where there is protection for
fish; also, a cover, a hole, or hiding place.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ The fox has
gone to <xex>holt</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>C. Kingsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holwe</ent>⟦br⟧
